Segment results consist of costs directly attributable to a segment as well as those that can be allocated on a

depreciation, amortisation, interests and income taxes (called “Recurring EBITDA”). This measurement basis excludes the effect of expenditure from the operating segments such as goodwill impairment that are not

expected to recur regularly in every reporting year.
